ate, gets it back on settle/timeout)\n    94→- `treasury` passed explicitly to settle builder (clock worker reads from config)\n    95→- `pnpm lint` (18 packages): 0 errors, 128 pre-existing warnings\n    96→- `pnpm typecheck` (18 packages): 0 errors\n    97→\n    98→## Iteration 4 — 2026-03-17T19:01:35Z — OK\n    99→- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n   100→\n   101→## Iteration 5 — CloseCallClockWorker\n   102→\n   103→**Item**: [backend] Create `closecall-clock.ts` — minute-boundary clock worker\n   104→\n   105→**Result**: PASS\n   106→\n   107→**Changes**:\n   108→- `services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`:\n   109→  - Factory function `createCloseCallClockWorker(deps)` → `CloseCallClockWorker` interface\n   110→  - Follows existing settlement worker pattern: setTimeout-based loop, start/stop/isRunning/tick\n   111→  - Tick aligns to minute boundaries + 2s offset (ensures candle has closed)\n   112→  - Each tick: (1) settle previous round if exists, (2) create new round with random 8-byte ID\n   113→  - Settlement logic: reads on-chain round + Pyth price to pre-determine outcome (Green/Red/Refund), passes correct remaining accounts to `buildCloseCallSettleRoundTx`\n   114→  - `sendAndConfirm()` helper with MAX_TX_RETRIES=3 and exponential delay (retry pattern)\n   115→  - `discoverActiveRound()` on start — scans for existing open rounds via `getProgramAccounts` (crash recovery)\n   116→  - Edge cases handled: no previous round, settlement failure (log + clear + continue), account already closed, non-Open phase\n   117→\n   118→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors, 128 pre-existing warnings) + `pnpm typecheck` (0 errors)\n   119→\n   120→## Iteration 5 — 2026-03-17T19:07:15Z — OK\n   121→- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n   122→\n   123→## Iteration 6 — Backend DB + API routes for Close Call\n   124→\n   125→**Item**: [backend] Extend DB with closecall_rounds table, add API routes, extend rounds/by-id\n   126→\n   127→**Result**: PASS\n   128→\n   129→**Changes**:\n   130→- `services/backend/migrations/005_closecall_rounds.sql`: New table `closecall_rounds` (round_id, pda, server_key, phase, open_price, open_price_expo, close_price, outcome, green_pool, red_pool, total_fee, green_entries JSONB, red_entries JSONB, settle_tx, created_at, settled_at). Separate from commit-reveal `rounds` table because closecall has no secret/commitment, is pari-mutuel (multiple players), and stores oracle prices.\n   131→- `services/backend/src/db.ts`: Added `CloseCallRound`, `CloseCallPhase`, `CloseCallOutcome` types. Added `InsertCloseCallRoundParams` interface. Added 5 new DB methods: `insertCloseCallRound`, `getCloseCallRound`, `getCloseCallCurrentRound`, `getCloseCallHistory`, `settleCloseCallRound`. Added `normalizeCloseCallRound` helper for BIGINT→number conversion.\n   132→- `services/backend/src/routes/closecall.ts`: New route file with `GET /closecall/current-round` (returns active round + pool state) and `GET /closecall/history` (last N settled rounds, default 20, max 100).\n   133→- `services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`: Extended `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` to fall back to `closecall_rounds` table when not found in commit-reveal `rounds` table. Added `formatCloseCallResponse()` for unified response shape.\n   134→- `services/backend/src/index.ts`: Registered closecall routes at `/closecall` prefix. Imported `createCloseCallRoutes`.\n   135→\n   136→**Design decisions**:\n   137→- Created separate `closecall_rounds` table rather than stretching the `rounds` table (which has NOT NULL on secret, commitment, side — fields that don't apply to oracle-resolved pari-mutuel games).\n   138→- Entries stored as JSONB arrays `[{player, amountLamports}]` — avoids join table complexity for max 64 entries.\n   139→- `/closecall` routes are NOT under `/fairness/` prefix (no JWT required for read-only pool state; the clock worker manages round lifecycle, not player-initiated create).\n   140→\n   141→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors, 128 pre-existing warnings) + `pnpm typecheck` (0 errors)\n   142→\n   143→## Iteration 6 — 2026-03-17T19:20:00Z — OK\n   144→- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n   145→\n   146→## Iteration 6 — 2026-03-17T19:13:19Z — OK\n   147→- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n   148→\n   149→## Iteration 7 — Wire CloseCallClockWorker into backend boot\n   150→\n   151→**Item**: [backend] Wire the CloseCallClockWorker into index.ts, add PYTH_BTC_USD_ACCOUNT env var\n   152→\n   153→**Result**: PASS\n   154→\n   155→**Changes**:\n   156→- `services/backend/src/config.ts`: Added `pythBtcUsdAccount` field to `Config` interface. Loaded from `PYTH_BTC_USD_ACCOUNT` env var with default `4cSM2e6rvbGQUFiJbqytoVMi5GgghSMr8LwVrT9VPSPo` (devnet BTC/USD Pyth push oracle price account).\n   157→- `services/backend/src/index.ts`: Imported `createCloseCallClockWorker`. Instantiated with `{ connection, serverKeypair, pythPriceAccount }` deps. Called `closeCallClock.start()` after settlement worker, before routes.\n   158→- `services/backend/.env`: Added `PYTH_BTC_USD_ACCOUNT=4cSM2e6rvbGQUFiJbqytoVMi5GgghSMr8LwVrT9VPSPo`.\n   159→\n   160→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors, 128 pre-existing warnings) + `pnpm typecheck` (0 errors)\n   161→\n   162→## Iteration 7 — 2026-03-17T19:17:15Z — OK\n   163→- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n   164→\n   165→## Iteration 8 — Deploy closecall program to devnet\n   166→\n   167→**Item**: [deploy] Deploy closecall program to devnet, initialize config, verify all instructions\n   168→\n   169→**Result**: PASS\n   170→\n   171→**Changes**:\n   172→- Deployed closecall program to devnet: `8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA`\n   173→  - Deploy method: `solana program deploy --use-rpc` (TPU DNS fails in container; used RPC-only mode)\n   174→  - Deploy tx: `45Dk3MNWshs4ZNrtPcAB6Rq6wHwSGskq2h66vwXc4uDzwEstutiT6UGPPWtfhhRBgZEFTGXKc2NST8PWdh8AGeoR`\n   175→- Initialized CloseCallConfig PDA (`6HkFfk5jWP4Qa9DPVoxRNEnU64qu7QnGQCBfs2y6Yadk`):\n   176→  - Treasury: `A