{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019g1fz37RyReuh9CSNW9zfa","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide a thorough summary.\n\n## Exploration Complete: Close Call Frontend Feature\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Close Call frontend feature. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **CloseCallContext.tsx - Full Mock Mode Analysis**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`\n\n**Mock Mode Status**: **NO MOCK MODE SUPPORT IN CloseCallContext**. The context does NOT check for `VITE_MOCK_MODE`. Instead:\n\n- **Live-only architecture**: All data flows from a real backend API\n- **Backend URL**: Reads from `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (default: `http://127.0.0.1:3100`)\n- **Real dependencies**: \n  - Uses real Pyth price subscription (`usePriceSubscription(\"BTC\")`)\n  - Polls backend for rounds every 2 seconds via `fetchCurrentRound()`\n  - Builds real Anchor transactions with `buildPlaceBetTx()` using the on-chain Closecall program\n  - Uses real wallet connection (`useWallet()`)\n\n**When no backend is available**: The page shows:\n- `loading: true` on initial mount\n- \"Loading chart...\" spinner in the main area\n- Once the first poll times out (~2 seconds), `currentRound` becomes `null`\n- The page gracefully degrades: sidebar displays \"Connect Wallet\" (if disconnected), empty chart area, no betting controls\n\n**Data flow without backend**:\n1. Initial state: `loading = true`\n2. First `fetchCurrentRound()` fails → returns `null`\n3. After setLoading(false), UI shows loading spinner\n4. On next poll interval, round stays `null`\n5. No error message displayed — silent degradation\n\n---\n\n### 2. **CloseCallPage.tsx - UI Structure**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx`\n\n**Page Layout**:\n- **Main area** (left/center):\n  - Candlestick chart with live price (from Pyth)\n  - Progress bar showing betting window (white) vs locked phase (gray)\n  - Result banner when a round completes\n  - Banner: \"Will the current candle close GREEN or RED?\"\n\n- **Sidebar** (right):\n  1. **Bet Amount Input** — text field + ½, 2×, MAX buttons (min 0.001 SOL, max 100 SOL)\n  2. **Side Selector** — GREEN/RED buttons (disabled when no active round or user already bet)\n  3. **Pool Distribution** — stacked bar chart showing green/red pool split, odds multiplier (~X.XXx), total pool, and user's active bet stats if any\n  4. **Payout Received** (conditional) — shown after round settles if user won\n  5. **Round Info** — Round ID (last 12 chars), Oracle (Pyth BTC/USD)\n\n- **History Modal**:\n  - Triggered by clicking history entries in GameLayout\n  - Shows: round stats, candle data (OHLC), outcome, payout, settlement TX\n  - Link to deep-dive round details page: `/close-call/{roundId}`\n\n**When disconnected**: \"Connect Wallet\" button instead of side selector\n\n**When betting locked**: Side selector disabled, chart shows \"BETTING LOCKED\" in progress label\n\n**When round settles**: \n- `completedRound` state triggers `RoundResultBanner` overlay\n- Shows outcome (GREEN WINS / RED WINS / REFUND)\n- Shows user result (You Won! / You Lost / Bet refunded)\n- Payout amount displayed\n- Dismissible\n\n---\n\n### 3. **mock-simulation.ts Status**\n\n**File**: **DELETED** — No mock-simulation.ts file exists.\n\n**Evidence**: File tree shows only:\n- `/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`\n- `/components/` (6 files)\n- `/hooks/index.ts` (exports only `useCloseCall`)\n- `/data/btc-candles.json` (static JSON, not imported by context)\n- `/utils/payout-calculator.ts`\n- `/types.ts`\n\nThe `btc-candles.json` is **unused** — no import references exist in the codebase for it. It appears to be leftover scaffolding.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **No Backend Connection — Page Behavior**\n\n**Scenario**: `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` unreachable\n\n1. **Initial load**: Shows \"Loading chart...\" spinner (because `loading = true`)\n2. **First poll (2s)**: `fetchCurrentRound()` returns `null` → page sets `loading = false`\n3. **UI state**:\n   - `currentRound = null`\n   - Chart area shows spinner forever (waiting for recentCandles to populate)\n   - Sidebar shows \"Connect Wallet\" (if disconnected)\n   - If connected: BetAmountInput enabled, but SideSelector disabled (no `isBettingOpen`)\n4. **No error message**: Silent failure — user sees loading state indefinitely\n5. **Pyth price subscription still works**: If connected to live RPC, the chart will show `currentPrice` updating, but no candles (because `btcPrice` alone doesn't create Candle objects — context builds candles from live price ticks)\n\n**User experience gap**: Player sees \"Loading chart...\" but page never recovers if backend is down.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **types.ts — Current State**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/types.ts`\n\n**Types Summary**:\n```typescript\n// Core types\nexport type BetSide = \"green\" | \"red\";\nexport type RoundPhase = \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\";\nexport type CandleOutcome = \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\";\n\n// Data structures\ninterface Candle { open, high, low, close, openTime, closeTime }\ninterface PlayerBet { address, side, amount (SOL), timestamp }\ninterface PoolState { greenPool, redPool, totalPool, playerCount, greenBets[], redBets[] }\ninterface Round {\n  id, phase, pool, createdAt, bettingEndsAt, resolvedAt,\n  outcome, openPrice, closePrice, settleTx\n}\n\n// Context interface\ninterface CloseCallContextValue {\n  // State\n  currentRound, completedRound, recentCandles, currentPrice, candleProgress, userHistory,\n  pendingAmount, pendingSide, userBet, loading, placingBet,\n  // Actions\n  setPendingAmount, setPendingSide, placeBet, adjustBetAmount, clearCompletedRound,\n  // Computed\n  potentialPayout, userOdds, refreshRound\n}\n\n// Constants\nDEFAULT_BET_AMOUNT = 0.5\nMIN_BET_AMOUNT = 0.001\nMAX_BET_AMOUNT = 100\nPLATFORM_FEE = 0.03 (3%)\nBETTING_WINDOW_MS = 30000 (first 30s of each candle)\nCANDLE_DURATION_MS = 60000 (1-minute candles)\n```\n\n**No mock data types** — all types assume real on-chain data from backend + Pyth.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Component Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Behavior |\n|------|---------|--------------|\n| **CandlestickChart.tsx** | Renders lightweight-charts candlestick + price panel | Displays history candles (muted), current candle (vibrant), progress bar, betting window countdown |\n| **BetAmountInput.tsx** | SOL input + quick-adjust buttons | Clamps to [0.001, 100], enforces min on blur, disables when user already bet |\n| **SideSelector.tsx** | GREEN/RED side buttons | Shows \"Joining...\" while transaction pending, disables opposite side during placement |\n| **PoolDistribution.tsx** | Pool bar chart + odds + user bet stats | Shows win/loss animations when round completes |\n| **ActiveBetView.tsx** | Detailed user bet card | Shows stake, share, potential win, multiplier, phase text |\n| **RoundResultOverlay.tsx** | Full-screen result popup | Win animation (stars + coins), outcome candle visual, payout text, auto-dismisses after 5s |\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Key Design Decisions (No Mocks)**\n\n✅ **Real throughout**: Pyth oracle → Anchor program → Backend API → Context → UI\n\n❌ **No mock mode**: No conditional rendering based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE`\n\n❌ **No fallback data**: `btc-candles.json` is unused\n\n✅ **Graceful degradation**: Missing backend = loading spinner (not crash, but poor UX)\n\n✅ **Commit-reveal** matching: Aligns with on-chain Closecall program (Pyth oracle pushes prices; on-chain resolves outcome)\n\n---\n\n### **Files to Reference**\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx` — Backend integration, Pyth subscription, transaction building\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx` — Main UI layout, state management\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallRoundPage.tsx` — Deep-dive round details page (fetches from backend `/fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}`)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/types.ts` — Type definitions (all real data)\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/utils/payout-calculator.ts` — Pari-mutuel math (3% fee, split winning pool)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1f2a6b06aceb6525 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 87374\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 66722</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d69f4c8-14e7-4d13-b2b6-b269933f82f3","uuid":"6e4ba27a-d68f-475d-ab0a-7d89d094283f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the close-call frontend feature at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/`. I need to understand:\n1. Read CloseCallContext.tsx fully - how does it work in mock mode? What happens when VITE_MOCK_MODE=true? Are there any mock data paths left?\n2. Read CloseCallPage.tsx - what does the UI render?\n3. Check if mock-simulation.ts still exists or was deleted\n4. What does the page show when there's no backend connection?\n5. Check types.ts for the current state of types\n\nBe thorough.","agentId":"a1f2a6b06aceb6525","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide a thorough summary.\n\n## Exploration Complete: Close Call Frontend Feature\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Close Call frontend feature. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **CloseCallContext.tsx - Full Mock Mode Analysis**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`\n\n**Mock Mode Status**: **NO MOCK MODE SUPPORT IN CloseCallContext**. The context does NOT check for `VITE_MOCK_MODE`. Instead:\n\n- **Live-only architecture**: All data flows from a real backend API\n- **Backend URL**: Reads from `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (default: `http://127.0.0.1:3100`)\n- **Real dependencies**: \n  - Uses real Pyth price subscription (`usePriceSubscription(\"BTC\")`)\n  - Polls backend for rounds every 2 seconds via `fetchCurrentRound()`\n  - Builds real Anchor transactions with `buildPlaceBetTx()` using the on-chain Closecall program\n  - Uses real wallet connection (`useWallet()`)\n\n**When no backend is available**: The page shows:\n- `loading: true` on initial mount\n- \"Loading chart...\" spinner in the main area\n- Once the first poll times out (~2 seconds), `currentRound` becomes `null`\n- The page gracefully degrades: sidebar displays \"Connect Wallet\" (if disconnected), empty chart area, no betting controls\n\n**Data flow without backend**:\n1. Initial state: `loading = true`\n2. First `fetchCurrentRound()` fails → returns `null`\n3. After setLoading(false), UI shows loading spinner\n4. On next poll interval, round stays `null`\n5. No error message displayed — silent degradation\n\n---\n\n### 2. **CloseCallPage.tsx - UI Structure**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx`\n\n**Page Layout**:\n- **Main area** (left/center):\n  - Candlestick chart with live price (from Pyth)\n  - Progress bar showing betting window (white) vs locked phase (gray)\n  - Result banner when a round completes\n  - Banner: \"Will the current candle close GREEN or RED?\"\n\n- **Sidebar** (right):\n  1. **Bet Amount Input** — text field + ½, 2×, MAX buttons (min 0.001 SOL, max 100 SOL)\n  2. **Side Selector** — GREEN/RED buttons (disabled when no active round or user already bet)\n  3. **Pool Distribution** — stacked bar chart showing green/red pool split, odds multiplier (~X.XXx), total pool, and user's active bet stats if any\n  4. **Payout Received** (conditional) — shown after round settles if user won\n  5. **Round Info** — Round ID (last 12 chars), Oracle (Pyth BTC/USD)\n\n- **History Modal**:\n  - Triggered by clicking history entries in GameLayout\n  - Shows: round stats, candle data (OHLC), outcome, payout, settlement TX\n  - Link to deep-dive round details page: `/close-call/{roundId}`\n\n**When disconnected**: \"Connect Wallet\" button instead of side selector\n\n**When betting locked**: Side selector disabled, chart shows \"BETTING LOCKED\" in progress label\n\n**When round settles**: \n- `completedRound` state triggers `RoundResultBanner` overlay\n- Shows outcome (GREEN WINS / RED WINS / REFUND)\n- Shows user result (You Won! / You Lost / Bet refunded)\n- Payout amount displayed\n- Dismissible\n\n---\n\n### 3. **mock-simulation.ts Status**\n\n**File**: **DELETED** — No mock-simulation.ts file exists.\n\n**Evidence**: File tree shows only:\n- `/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`\n- `/components/` (6 files)\n- `/hooks/index.ts` (exports only `useCloseCall`)\n- `/data/btc-candles.json` (static JSON, not imported by context)\n- `/utils/payout-calculator.ts`\n- `/types.ts`\n\nThe `btc-candles.json` is **unused** — no import references exist in the codebase for it. It appears to be leftover scaffolding.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **No Backend Connection — Page Behavior**\n\n**Scenario**: `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` unreachable\n\n1. **Initial load**: Shows \"Loading chart...\" spinner (because `loading = true`)\n2. **First poll (2s)**: `fetchCurrentRound()` returns `null` → page sets `loading = false`\n3. **UI state**:\n   - `currentRound = null`\n   - Chart area shows spinner forever (waiting for recentCandles to populate)\n   - Sidebar shows \"Connect Wallet\" (if disconnected)\n   - If connected: BetAmountInput enabled, but SideSelector disabled (no `isBettingOpen`)\n4. **No error message**: Silent failure — user sees loading state indefinitely\n5. **Pyth price subscription still works**: If connected to live RPC, the chart will show `currentPrice` updating, but no candles (because `btcPrice` alone doesn't create Candle objects — context builds candles from live price ticks)\n\n**User experience gap**: Player sees \"Loading chart...\" but page never recovers if backend is down.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **types.ts — Current State**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/types.ts`\n\n**Types Summary**:\n```typescript\n// Core types\nexport type BetSide = \"green\" | \"red\";\nexport type RoundPhase = \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\";\nexport type CandleOutcome = \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\";\n\n// Data structures\ninterface Candle { open, high, low, close, openTime, closeTime }\ninterface PlayerBet { address, side, amount (SOL), timestamp }\ninterface PoolState { greenPool, redPool, totalPool, playerCount, greenBets[], redBets[] }\ninterface Round {\n  id, phase, pool, createdAt, bettingEndsAt, resolvedAt,\n  outcome, openPrice, closePrice, settleTx\n}\n\n// Context interface\ninterface CloseCallContextValue {\n  // State\n  currentRound, completedRound, recentCandles, currentPrice, candleProgress, userHistory,\n  pendingAmount, pendingSide, userBet, loading, placingBet,\n  // Actions\n  setPendingAmount, setPendingSide, placeBet, adjustBetAmount, clearCompletedRound,\n  // Computed\n  potentialPayout, userOdds, refreshRound\n}\n\n// Constants\nDEFAULT_BET_AMOUNT = 0.5\nMIN_BET_AMOUNT = 0.001\nMAX_BET_AMOUNT = 100\nPLATFORM_FEE = 0.03 (3%)\nBETTING_WINDOW_MS = 30000 (first 30s of each candle)\nCANDLE_DURATION_MS = 60000 (1-minute candles)\n```\n\n**No mock data types** — all types assume real on-chain data from backend + Pyth.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Component Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Behavior |\n|------|---------|--------------|\n| **CandlestickChart.tsx** | Renders lightweight-charts candlestick + price panel | Displays history candles (muted), current candle (vibrant), progress bar, betting window countdown |\n| **BetAmountInput.tsx** | SOL input + quick-adjust buttons | Clamps to [0.001, 100], enforces min on blur, disables when user already bet |\n| **SideSelector.tsx** | GREEN/RED side buttons | Shows \"Joining...\" while transaction pending, disables opposite side during placement |\n| **PoolDistribution.tsx** | Pool bar chart + odds + user bet stats | Shows win/loss animations when round completes |\n| **ActiveBetView.tsx** | Detailed user bet card | Shows stake, share, potential win, multiplier, phase text |\n| **RoundResultOverlay.tsx** | Full-screen result popup | Win animation (stars + coins), outcome candle visual, payout text, auto-dismisses after 5s |\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Key Design Decisions (No Mocks)**\n\n✅ **Real throughout**: Pyth oracle → Anchor program → Backend API → Context → UI\n\n❌ **No mock mode**: No conditional rendering based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE`\n\n❌ **No fallback data**: `btc-candles.json` is unused\n\n✅ **Graceful degradation**: Missing backend = loading spinner (not crash, but poor UX)\n\n✅ **Commit-reveal** matching: Aligns with on-chain Closecall program (Pyth oracle pushes prices; on-chain resolves outcome)\n\n---\n\n### **Files to Reference**\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx` — Backend integration, Pyth subscription, transaction building\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx` — Main UI layout, state management\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallRoundPage.tsx` — Deep-dive round details page (fetches from backend `/fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}`)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/types.ts` — Type definitions (all real data)\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/utils/payout-calculator.ts` — Pari-mutuel math (3% fee, split winning pool)"}],"totalDurationMs":66722,"totalTokens"